article.headline: Lehigh 60, Dartmouth 57
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Jose Olivero and Ra Tiah each scored 16 points for Lehigh, and the Mountainhawks held on for a 60-57 victory over Dartmouth on Saturday. Lehigh (6-3) made six-of-seven free throws in the final 33 seconds to counter a late Dartmouth rally that included 3-point baskets by Steve Callahan and Mike Lang. Trailing 56-49, the Big Green (2-6) Callahan started Dartmouth's last rush with a driving layup. After two Lehigh free throws, Callahan banged home a three, making it 58-54 with 22 seconds left. The Mountainhawks missed a free throw and Lang followed with a 3-pointer with 16 seconds remaining, pulling Dartmouth within 58-57. But Olivero hit two free throws with nine seconds left, and Dartmouth's Leon Pattman missed an off-balance attempt at the buzzer. Pattman finished with 16 points.
